{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:psalms.71",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 71,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 71 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:1",
      "text": "A Psalm of instruction for Asaph. Wherefore hast thou rejected us, O God, for ever? wherefore is thy wrath kindled against the sheep of thy pasture?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:2",
      "text": "Remember thy congregation which thou hast purchased from the beginning; thou didst ransom the rod of thine inheritance; this mount Sion wherein thou hast dwelt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:3",
      "text": "Lift up thine hands against their pride continually; because of all that the enemy has done wickedly in thy holy places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:4",
      "text": "And they that hate thee have boasted in the midst of thy feast; they have set up their standards for signs,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:5",
      "text": "ignorantly as it were in the entrance above;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:6",
      "text": "they cut down its doors at once with axes as in a wood of trees; they have broken it down with hatchet and stone cutter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:7",
      "text": "They have burnt thy sanctuary with fire to the ground; they have profaned the",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:8",
      "text": "They have said in their heart, even all their kindred together, Come, let us abolish the feasts of the Lord from the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:9",
      "text": "We have not seen our signs; there is no longer a prophet; and God will not know us any more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:10",
      "text": "How long, O God, shall the enemy reproach? shall the enemy provoke thy name for ever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:11",
      "text": "Wherefore turnest thou away thine hand, and thy right hand from the midst of thy bosom for ever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:12",
      "text": "But God is our King of old; he has wrought salvation in the midst of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:13",
      "text": "Thou didst establish the sea, in thy might, thou didst break to pieces the heads of the dragons in the water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:14",
      "text": "Thou didst break to pieces the heads of the dragon; thou didst give him for meat to the Ethiopian nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:15",
      "text": "Thou didst cleave fountains and torrents; thou driedst up mighty rivers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:16",
      "text": "The day is thine, and the night is thine; thou hast prepared the sun and the moon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:17",
      "text": "Thou hast made all the borders of the earth; thou hast made summer and spring.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:18",
      "text": "Remember this thy creation: an enemy has reproached the Lord, and a foolish people has provoked thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:19",
      "text": "Deliver not to the wild beasts a soul that gives praise to thee: forget not for ever the souls of thy poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:20",
      "text": "Look upon thy covenant: for the dark places of the earth are filled with the habitations of iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:21",
      "text": "Let not the afflicted and shamed one be rejected: the poor and needy shall praise thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:22",
      "text": "Arise, O God, plead thy cause: remember thy reproaches that come from the foolish one all the day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:23",
      "text": "Forget not the voice of thy suppliants: let the pride of them that hate thee continually ascend before thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:24",
      "text": "Thou hast guided me by thy counsel, and thou hast taken me to thyself with glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:25",
      "text": "For what have I in heaven but thee? and what have I desired upon the earth beside thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:26",
      "text": "My heart and my flesh have failed: but God is the strength of my heart, and God is my portion for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:27",
      "text": "For, behold, they that remove themselves far from thee shall perish: thou hast destroyed every one that goes a whoring from thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.71.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 71,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 71:28",
      "text": "But it is good for me to cleave close to God, to put my trust in the Lord; that I may proclaim all thy praises in the gates of the daughter of Sion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
